<title type="html"><![CDATA[[SOLVED] My emulator's PPU frame is 200 clocks short?]]></title>

<content type="html" xml:base="http://forums.nesdev.com/viewtopic.php?t=8591&amp;p=89688#p89688"><![CDATA[
Yep, now I _know_ that the NES needs it's I flag set on reset/power-on. Everything works fine now ... and I'm passing all vbl_nmi_timing tests.<br /><br />Now I'm just failing some sprite-overflow and APU tests ... but those are not that obscure so I think I will have them fixed sooner or later <img src="http://forums.nesdev.com/images/smilies/icon_wink.gif" alt=";)" title="Wink" /><br /><br />Edit: At first all this PPU NMI stuff seemed to be very complex ... I tried to implement the stuff using 'hacks' ... but after some analysis everything turned out to be damn simple. Hopefully the APU will evolve the same (some timing issues and DMC is still missing).<br /><br />Dunno why I started to do a NES emulator ... already coded a GB/GBC emu and a SID player. Maybe it's just because I want to see my NTSC emu in an emulator ... <br />... and I don't sacrifice anything for speed. The emu will need a dual core CPU &gt;= 1.5GHz, a OpenGL 3.3 capable graphics card (for NTSC modulation/demodulation) and a sound card providing stable low latency audio streams (&lt;512 sample frame buffers).<br /><br />About the 6502 core: cycle accurate (without half-cycles).<br /><br />For the sound: as I'm very familiar with DSP it's of course generated at the original sample rate and resampled correctly.<br /><br />NTSC emulation is fully done in pixel shaders. The graphics card recieves a texture containing 9 bit original nes palette values (282x240 pixels), generates a NES luma/chroma signal and demodulates it. I won't emulate the BG-disabled-skip-idle-cycle thing because I want flicker free images and so I'm 'field merging' stuff. <br /><br />... maybe it gets finished sometime ... still have lot's of stuff to do ... but it's great working with a 6502 machine again <img src="http://forums.nesdev.com/images/smilies/icon_biggrin.gif" alt=":D" title="Very Happy" /><br /><br />Well ... we all think we're special and doing thing different, arent we?^^<br /><br />(Just to prove that I have got sound^^ : <a href="http://dl.dropbox.com/u/11133993/guardian_legend.flac" class="postlink">http://dl.dropbox.com/u/11133993/guardian_legend.flac</a> <img src="http://forums.nesdev.com/images/smilies/icon_biggrin.gif" alt=":D" title="Very Happy" /> )<p>Statistics: Posted by <a href="http://forums.nesdev.com/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=5175">neet</a> — Tue Feb 07, 2012 11:36 am</p><hr />
